        <item rdf:about="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41567-026-03229-z">
            <title>Loop-current order in kagome metals</title>
            <link>https://www.nature.com/articles/s41567-026-03229-z</link>
            <content:encoded>
                &lt;p&gt;Nature Physics, Published online: 16 April 2026; &lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41567-026-03229-z"&gt;doi:10.1038/s41567-026-03229-z&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;Loop-current states represent a rare magnetic order driven by orbital motion, rather than by spin. This Perspective examines their symmetry, microscopic origins, detection challenges and interplay with other orders in kagome superconductors.</content:encoded>
            <dc:title>Loop-current order in kagome metals</dc:title>
            <dc:creator>Rafael M. Fernandes</dc:creator><dc:creator>Turan Birol</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mengxing Ye</dc:creator><dc:creator>David Vanderbilt</dc:creator>
            <dc:identifier>doi:10.1038/s41567-026-03229-z</dc:identifier>
